                "<p>The power of a quotient rule allows us to quickly find the result of a quotient raised to an exponent:</p>",
                "<p>When we have a quotient raised to an exponent, <b>distribute the exponent</b> to both the numerator and the denominator.</p>",
                "<p>Using the power of a quotient rule, we get:</p>",
                {
                    Example: "Math",
                    Content: '(\\frac{2}{5})^3 = \\frac{2^3}{5^3} = \\frac{8}{125}'
